<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
	<id>63783</id>
	<title>ASKLIBREOFFICE: Erroneous "(this field is required)" error message in Feedback Contact Form</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">---------Problem description---------</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">While trying to send a rather long message through the AskLO "Give us feedback" contact form I was met with the following error message:</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">(this field is required)</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">This message was erroneous of course because the field was everything but empty.</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.2">Only after shortening the message by a few sentences I was able to send it on its way.</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.3">I suspect that the error message is related to the message character count.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="5">
			<sentence id="5.1">---------Steps to reproduce---------</sentence>
			<sentence id="5.2">1 Make sure you are logged in to ask.libreoffice.org</sentence>
			<sentence id="5.3">2 Head to http://ask.libreoffice.org/en/feedback/?next=/en/question/7848/is-this-an-asklibo-answer-or-a-junk-mail/</sentence>
			<sentence id="5.4">3 Copy and paste a long passage of text into the message box (&gt;1000 characters should be enough)</sentence>
			<sentence id="5.5">4 Include an apologetic note to the web-administration team and make sure to clarify that you are sending them this message for test purposes only (just in case it does make it through ;))</sentence>
			<sentence id="6.5">5 Hit "Send"</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="7">
			<sentence id="7.1">------------Suggestion------------</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="8">
			<sentence id="8.1">If it really is the character count that triggers this error notify the user that he hit the character limit.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
